<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/dbf114617d9cdf364e2095d126698fce.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 3 and c = 6. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.2</li><li>30.0</li><li>60.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}^{{2}}={3}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{36}={9}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{36}-{9}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{27}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{27}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5.1961524227066}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5.2}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{6}}\right)}}}\approx{30}\approx{30}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{3}}{{6}}\right)}}}\approx{60}\approx{60}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

